    "scope": "repo",
    "content": "PRISM daemon health depends on keeping authoritative runtime state, bounded serving projections, and cold analytical evidence separate. Symbol-level co-change is analytical evidence, not hot runtime history: persisting unbounded pairwise co-change or hydrating it into HistoryStore makes cache growth, startup memory, and refresh lock contention explode. Co-change should stay bounded in serving projections, while any colder evidence must remain off the daemon hot path.",
